# Docs

## Tech stack

- **Runtime:** Node.js 24 with TypeScript (ESM, strict mode)
- **Bot framework:** Grammy with conversations plugin
- **Database:** SQLite (better-sqlite3, WAL mode)
- **Testing:** Vitest (504 tests)
- **Deployment:** Docker, multi-stage build

## Architecture

```
DeFiLlama API → Fetcher → Filter → SQLite Cache → Risk Scoring → Alert Engine → Telegram
```

Data flows in one direction. The bot polls DeFiLlama every 5 minutes, filters down to ~3,800 eligible pools, scores each one on six risk factors, and pushes matches to subscribed users.

## Risk scoring model

Each pool receives a composite score based on:

| Factor | Weight | Source |
|--------|--------|--------|
| APY / volatility | Base formula | DeFiLlama |
| TVL quality | Multiplier | DeFiLlama |
| 7-day trend | Multiplier | DeFiLlama |
| Impermanent loss | 0.5x penalty | DeFiLlama |
| Pool maturity | Multiplier | Internal (snapshot count) |
| Token security | 0.0–1.0 multiplier | GoPlus API |
| Protocol metadata | Tier classification | DeFiLlama protocols |

## Self-hosting

```bash
git clone https://github.com/goncalovelosa/yield-radar.git
cd yield-radar
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
docker compose up -d
```

## API sources

- **DeFiLlama** — Pool data, APY, TVL, protocol metadata
- **GoPlus** — Token security analysis (honeypot, malicious contracts, tax)

